<h2>Usage guidelines</h2>
<ul>
    <li>Use tables for structured data that benefits from row/column organization</li>
    <li>Always include table headers for accessibility</li>
    <li>Use sortable tables when users need to reorder data</li>
    <li>Use expandable rows for hierarchical or detailed information</li>
    <li>Keep tables responsive - consider horizontal scrolling on small screens</li>
    <li>Use appropriate table classes: <code>table-striped</code>, <code>table-hover</code>, <code>table-bordered</code></li>
    <li>Include badges or status indicators for quick visual scanning</li>
</ul>

<h2>Accessibility</h2>
<ul>
    <li>Always use <code>&lt;thead&gt;</code> and <code>&lt;tbody&gt;</code> elements</li>
    <li>Use <code>&lt;th&gt;</code> for header cells, not <code>&lt;td&gt;</code></li>
    <li>For sortable columns, include <code>role="button"</code> and <code>tabindex="0"</code></li>
    <li>Provide <code>aria-label</code> for sortable column headers</li>
    <li>Use <code>aria-expanded</code> for expandable rows</li>
    <li>Ensure sufficient colour contrast for all text</li>
</ul>

<h2>JavaScript for toggle rows</h2>
<p>
    Tables with toggle rows require JavaScript to change the icon when expanded/collapsed.
</p>

<pre><code>&lt;script&gt;
    $(document).ready(function() {
        // Handle icon toggle for expandable rows
        $('[id^="area-"]').on('show.bs.collapse', function() {
            var targetId = $(this).attr('id');
            var row = $('tr[data-target="#' + targetId + '"]');
            var icon = row.find('.collapse-icon');
            icon.removeClass('fa-plus-circle').addClass('fa-minus-circle');
        });

        $('[id^="area-"]').on('hide.bs.collapse', function() {
            var targetId = $(this).attr('id');
            var row = $('tr[data-target="#' + targetId + '"]');
            var icon = row.find('.collapse-icon');
            icon.removeClass('fa-minus-circle').addClass('fa-plus-circle');
        });
    });
&lt;/script&gt;</code></pre>

<script nonce="@Context.Items["Nonce"]">
    $(document).ready(function() {
        // Handle icon toggle for expandable rows in example
        $('#area-1').on('show.bs.collapse', function() {
            var row = $('tr[data-target="#area-1"]');
            var icon = row.find('.collapse-icon');
            icon.removeClass('fa-plus-circle').addClass('fa-minus-circle');
        });

        $('#area-1').on('hide.bs.collapse', function() {
            var row = $('tr[data-target="#area-1"]');
            var icon = row.find('.collapse-icon');
            icon.removeClass('fa-minus-circle').addClass('fa-plus-circle');
        });
    });
</script>
